+# Dynamic Memory Sparsification (DMS)
+
+**Technical Reference for Implementation — March 2026**
+
+---
+
+## What DMS Does
+
+DMS compresses the KV cache during LLM inference by training the model to decide which tokens to keep and which to discard. During autoregressive generation, the KV cache grows linearly with sequence length, consuming VRAM and slowing inference because attention is memory-bandwidth-bound. DMS teaches the model a per-head eviction policy where each attention head learns to emit a binary keep/evict signal for every token. Tokens marked for eviction are not removed immediately but retained for a configurable delay window (512 tokens by default), giving the model time to absorb their information into newer representations before the actual eviction occurs.
+
+The retrofit training takes approximately 1,000 steps using knowledge distillation (forward KL divergence between frozen teacher and student logits). The result is 8x KV cache compression with accuracy matching or exceeding the uncompressed model on reasoning benchmarks (AIME 24, GPQA, LiveCodeBench, MATH-500). The practical benefit is either fitting longer contexts into the same VRAM or serving more concurrent requests on the same hardware.
+
+---
+
+## Paper
+
+- **Title:** Inference-Time Hyper-Scaling with KV Cache Compression
+- **Authors:** Adrian Łańcucki, Konrad Staniszewski, Piotr Nawrot, Edoardo M. Ponti (NVIDIA / University of Edinburgh)
+- **Published:** NeurIPS 2025
+- **arXiv:** [2506.05345](https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.05345)
+
+---
+
+## Key Results (from paper)
+
+| Benchmark | Qwen3-8B | DMS-8x | Delta | Notes |
+|-----------|----------|--------|-------|-------|
+| GPQA Diamond | 58.8 | 57.6 | -1.2 | Science |
+| MMLU-Pro | 74.2 | 73.5 | -0.7 | General |
+| AIME 2024 | 75.0 | 73.0 | -2.0 | Math |
+| MATH-500 | 95.1 | 95.5 | +0.4 | Math |
+| HumanEval | 87.8 | 89.6 | +1.8 | Code |
+| RULER 64K | 69.2 | 76.2 | +7.0 | Long ctx |
+| RULER 128K | 25.0 | 21.4 | -3.6 | Long ctx |
+
+Qwen-R1 32B with DMS scored 12.0 points higher than baseline on AIME 24 under equivalent memory bandwidth constraints. Throughput increased up to 5x on Qwen3-8B at equivalent accuracy.
+
