+|---------|----------------|---------------------|---------------------|
+| 4K | 3.457s | 1.260s (2.74x) | 3.083s (1.12x) |
+| 8K | 7.922s | 1.348s (5.88x) | 5.795s (1.37x) |
+| 16K | 22.211s | 2.503s (8.88x) | 12.699s (1.75x) |
+| 32K | OOM | 5.139s | 25.685s |
+
+### Peak VRAM (GB)
+
+| Context | Hub | FlexAttn | Triton |
+|---------|-----|----------|--------|
+| 4K | 16.89 GB | 16.84 GB | 15.99 GB |
+| 8K | 17.93 GB | 16.97 GB | 16.47 GB |
+| 16K | 20.07 GB | 17.21 GB | 17.48 GB |
+| 32K | OOM | 17.79 GB | 19.43 GB |
+
+FlexAttn (Model Optimizer) is the fastest prefill path. Decode speed is comparable across all variants (~20-42 tok/s).
+
+---
+
+## Adding DMS to a New Model Family
+
+From `ARCHITECTURE.md` in Model Optimizer. The core DMS operations are model-agnostic. Model-specific code provides Q/K/V projections and norms.
+
+1. Create a directory under `experimental/dms/models/your_model/` with configuration, modeling, extraction, and training entry point files.
+2. Extend the model's config class with DMS parameters (reference: `models/qwen3/configuration_qwen3_dms.py`).
+3. Override the attention forward pass to call `dms.core.prepare_attention_input` and `dms.attention.dms_attention`.
+4. Add `dms_proj_alpha` and `dms_proj_alpha_norm` layers to the attention module (if using `dms_separate_alpha=True`).
+5. Add a YAML config under `configs/`.
+6. Run training: `experimental/dms/scripts/train.sh` (reference configs for hyperparameters).
+
