Subject: [PATCH 03/22] Add DMS (Dynamic Memory Sparsification) Phase 1
 integration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements per-head KV cache eviction for DMS-trained models (8x
compression) using the batch×head flattening trick with standard
flash_attn_varlen_func — no custom CUDA kernels required.

Key components:
- DMSConfig: reads DMS params from HF config.json
- DMSState: per-layer circular buffer tracking eviction decisions,
  slot recycling via free list, per-head cache_seq_lens
- DMSFlashAttentionBackend/Impl: per-head decode via batch×head
  flattening, per-head cache writes via direct tensor indexing,
  prefill compaction via compute_prefill_survivors + compact_kv_cache
- Qwen3DMSForCausalLM: model variant extracting eviction decisions
  from Q projection (last dim, first head per GQA group)
- 30 CPU unit tests + 5 GPU integration tests (NF4 checkpoint)

Fixes found during integration:
- decisions dtype cast to long in circular buffer
- lazy import of DMSFlashAttentionBackend to avoid CUDA init in
  model inspection subprocess
- DMSFlashAttentionImpl inherits AttentionImpl for required interface
- registry _save_modelinfo_to_cache import moved inside try block

