From 819994162b9668e21ede93091dea6a18459f0afd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 10:03:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 05/22] Prevent block over-allocation for DMS requests
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DMS slot recycling keeps cache length bounded while num_tokens grows
linearly. Without this, the scheduler allocates blocks the worker
never uses — wasting memory that could serve other requests.

Worker reports effective cache length (max per-head seq_len from
DMSState) via ModelRunnerOutput each step. Scheduler stores it on
Request and kv_cache_manager uses it instead of num_tokens for block
allocation. Non-DMS requests are completely unaffected (field is None,
getattr falls through to original num_tokens).

---
 vllm/v1/core/kv_cache_manager.py   |  7 ++++-
 vllm/v1/core/sched/scheduler.py    |  8 ++++++
 vllm/v1/outputs.py                 |  4 +++
 vllm/v1/request.py                 |  5 ++++
 vllm/v1/worker/gpu_model_runner.py | 46 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 5 files changed, 69 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vllm/v1/core/kv_cache_manager.py b/vllm/v1/core/kv_cache_manager.py
