From 12493d73728a95548064d4812d6cc9281bd94f02 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 10:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 06/22] Fix DMS runtime and add diagnostic tests proving
 eviction works
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Critical fixes found via diagnostic testing:

- DMSConfig injection: pass directly from model to impl at init
  (get_current_vllm_config unavailable outside forward context)
- Cache update timing: set forward_includes_kv_cache_update=True
  so decisions are available when cache is written
- Per-head decode: loop over KV heads with single-head cache views
  (batch×head trick incompatible with vLLM's shared-head blocks)
- Layer name alignment: store decisions under ".attn" suffix to
  match Attention wrapper's layer_name
- Chunked prefill: skip compaction on intermediate chunks, init
  seq_lens uniformly instead

Diagnostic tests (test_dms_diagnostics.py) confirm DMS is working:
- 36/36 layers initialized with DMSState
- Prefill compaction: 1046 tokens → 512 cache entries (~2x)
- Per-head divergence: spread up to 21 across 35 layers
- Compression: avg 1.01-1.04x at 533 tokens (early in sequence)

Known perf issue: per-head decode loop is ~10x slower than standard
flash_attn (288 calls per step). Custom kernel needed for Phase 3.

