From f1b5067deaab2080a700228ba401b5c7716cd7a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 10:27:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 07/22] Add Triton paged decode kernel for DMS per-head
 attention

Replaces the per-KV-head flash_attn loop (288 calls/step on Qwen3-8B)
with a single Triton kernel launch per layer. Each program handles one
(request, query_head) pair, reading K/V from paged blocks at the specific
head index with per-head seq_lens.

Microbenchmark: 0.175ms/call at seq_len=512, 6.3ms/step across 36 layers.
End-to-end: 11.6 tok/s with DMS vs 24.5 tok/s without (2.1x overhead,
down from ~10x before). Remaining overhead is in cache update path.

Includes unit tests (9 passing) and benchmark script (kernel + e2e).

