From b59b61584fc0eca8a29585a033a0fe87f0dc1d15 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 10:39:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 08/22] Fuse DMS cache update into Triton kernel and reduce
 Python overhead
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cache update: replaces ~30 Python tensor ops per layer (get_slot_mapping,
block_table lookup, scatter writes, circular buffer update) with a single
Triton kernel launch. 134x faster (30.4 → 0.23 ms/tok).

Python overhead: inlines the DMS decode hot path to eliminate redundant
get_forward_context() lookups, lazy imports, and function call overhead.
Moves Triton kernel imports to module level.

Also eliminates GPU→CPU sync from nonzero() in update_decode by replacing
with fully vectorized torch.where, and caches torch.arange tensors.

End-to-end: 17.3 tok/s with DMS vs 24.5 tok/s without (1.42x overhead,
down from 2.0x at start of session). Remaining gap is mostly Triton
decode kernel vs flash_attn's optimized CUDA kernel.

