From ed9e7567c8cd00fcbfbd9b3a21f8ce7fc723ab2e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 11:03:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/22] Enable CUDAGraph support for DMS decode (2.5x speedup)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Change _cudagraph_support to UNIFORM_SINGLE_TOKEN_DECODE, enabling
  FULL CUDAGraph capture for decode batches
- Add phys_block < 0 guard in fused cache update kernel to skip padding
  requests during CUDAGraph replay with padded batch sizes
- Replace per-step GPU→CPU sync (per_head_seq_lens.max().item()) with
  fixed max_num_blocks computed once from block_table width
- Create DMSState eagerly on first decode for CUDAGraph capture warmup
- Results: DMS ON 43.4 tok/s (+CG) vs 17.3 tok/s (eager) = 2.5x faster

