From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 11:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 11/22] Add early return for padding in Triton decode kernel
 (70.3 tok/s)

Skip the entire decode loop for padding requests (seq_len <= 0) by
storing zeros and returning immediately. With CUDAGraph's padded batch
sizes, this avoids ~28K wasted loop iterations per kernel launch.

Results: DMS ON +CG 70.3 tok/s (was 43.4), only 1.17x overhead vs
DMS OFF +CG 82.0 tok/s. Runtime branch inside the loop was also
tried but caused 15x regression due to broken Triton loop pipelining.

---
 vllm/v1/attention/dms/triton_dms_decode.py | 44 +++++++++-------------
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vllm/v1/attention/dms/triton_dms_decode.py b/vllm/v1/attention/dms/triton_dms_decode.py
index 94dd5b370..fdc90f4c6 100644
