From 475a555f67cda74b718cb7cdefc8bef752311c9b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 11:27:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 12/22] Single-pass fused prefill: raw K/V attention +
 selective cache write
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Instead of writing all tokens to cache then compacting survivors,
use flash_attn with raw K/V (no block_table) and write only survivors
directly to contiguous cache positions. Eliminates reshape_and_cache
for all tokens + the gather/scatter compaction pass.

Falls back to two-pass for chunked prefill (max_query_len < max_seq_len).

Input throughput: 116.5 → 123.1 tok/s (1.32x → 1.25x overhead)
Decode throughput: 70.3 → 77.0 tok/s (1.17x → 1.06x overhead)

