From de5a7fd16a91dd2e15c55c75410dc79028fc19fa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 11:39:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 13/22] Split-K decode kernel: 83.2 tok/s, DMS now faster than
 baseline
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace sequential Triton decode kernel with Split-K two-stage approach
adapted from vLLM's triton_decode_attention.py. Key improvements:
- Split-K parallelism: KV cache split into NUM_KV_SPLITS=8 chunks
  processed by separate programs, reduced in stage 2
- Grouped head processing with tl.dot (tensor cores) instead of
  element-wise tl.sum
- num_warps=4, num_stages=2 tuning

Performance: 77.0 → 83.2 tok/s (+8%), now 0.98x vs DMS OFF (81.3).
Also reduce gpu_memory_utilization from 0.85-0.9 to 0.7 in tests/benchmarks
to prevent OOM when running multiple test files.

