From 965affc4ed082a77403c07ccd01dc5693b53fc4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 12:03:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 15/22] Block freeing: scheduler reclaims blocks after DMS
 compaction

After DMS compacts the KV cache, tail blocks become empty but were
never returned to the pool. This adds the full pipeline:

- Worker reports dms_effective_tokens (max per-head seq_len) to scheduler
- Scheduler computes needed blocks, frees excess via remove_tail_blocks
- Scheduler sends dms_blocks_to_trim in SchedulerOutput to worker
- Worker trims block_table.num_blocks_per_row before next append_row
- Allocation now uses dms_effective_tokens to avoid over-allocating

Verified: 32 blocks (512 tokens) freed for 1047-token request (~2x CR).
46 tests passing including new TestBlockFreeing diagnostic.

