From 8e5927af9b66436e9c8500c8d9d2a1f49f7ad624 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anonymous <anonymous@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Mar 2026 12:27:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 17/22] Copy-on-write prefix caching for DMS

Re-enable prefix caching with DMS by copying shared blocks to private
ones before compaction. Shared prefix blocks (ref_cnt > 1) are detected
during allocation, replaced with fresh blocks, and GPU KV data is copied
before forward() runs. DMS requests consume from prefix cache but never
contribute back (compacted blocks have per-request content).

- Scheduler: budget CoW blocks, replace shared blocks, skip cache_blocks
- Worker: batched GPU block copy + block table update in _update_states
- BlockTable: replace_block_ids helper for CoW remapping
- Tests: 3 prefix caching CoW tests (shared prefix, repeated prompt,
  sequential batches)

