+    Uses varied content to give DMS heads different eviction patterns,
+    which is more realistic than repeating the same sentence.
+    """
+    sections = [
+        # Science
+        "Quantum mechanics describes nature at the atomic scale. "
+        "Wave functions collapse upon measurement, producing definite outcomes. "
+        "The uncertainty principle limits simultaneous knowledge of position "
+        "and momentum. Entangled particles share correlations that persist "
+        "across arbitrary distances, violating Bell inequalities. ",
+        # History
+        "The Roman Empire spanned centuries of territorial expansion. "
+        "Augustus established the principate after decades of civil war. "
+        "Trade routes connected Rome to India and China via the Silk Road. "
+        "The fall of the Western Empire in 476 CE reshaped European politics. ",
+        # Mathematics
+        "Calculus provides tools for analyzing continuous change. "
+        "The fundamental theorem connects differentiation and integration. "
+        "Differential equations model physical systems from orbits to heat flow. "
+        "Linear algebra underpins machine learning and quantum computing. ",
+        # Technology
+        "Transformer architectures revolutionized natural language processing. "
+        "Self-attention computes pairwise token interactions in parallel. "
+        "Key-value caching avoids redundant computation during autoregressive "
+        "decoding. Memory-efficient attention reduces the quadratic cost. ",
+        # Biology
+        "DNA encodes genetic information in sequences of four nucleotides. "
+        "Transcription produces mRNA from DNA templates in the nucleus. "
+        "Ribosomes translate mRNA into proteins through codon recognition. "
+        "CRISPR-Cas9 enables precise genome editing at targeted loci. ",
+        # Economics
+        "Supply and demand curves determine market equilibrium prices. "
+        "Central banks adjust interest rates to manage inflation targets. "
+        "Fiscal policy uses government spending and taxation to stabilize "
+        "output. International trade follows comparative advantage principles. ",
+        # Philosophy
+        "Epistemology examines the nature and limits of human knowledge. "
+        "Empiricists argue that experience is the foundation of understanding. "
+        "Rationalists maintain that reason alone can reveal certain truths. "
+        "Pragmatists evaluate beliefs by their practical consequences. ",
+        # Geography
+        "Tectonic plates drift on the asthenosphere at centimeters per year. "
+        "Subduction zones generate volcanic arcs and deep ocean trenches. "
+        "Mid-ocean ridges produce new oceanic crust through seafloor spreading. "
+        "Continental collisions build mountain ranges like the Himalayas. ",
+    ]
