Replace per-head Python loops in write_survivors_to_cache,
compact_kv_cache, and initialize_dms_state_from_prefill with
fully vectorized ops using cumsum-derived destination indices.

Key changes:
- Single .nonzero() call across all (token, head) pairs
- cumsum replaces 8x per-head searchsorted + nonzero
- Bulk circular buffer write via transpose
- Removed .cpu() GPU sync in compact_kv_cache

Prefill throughput: 964.8 → 1087.4 tok/s (+12.7%)

